00536 //{
00537     // I think the key to parsing this properly is having the input "Person" parse properly.
00538     //
00539     // An expression can contain a 'TypeClauseNode', so it ought to be an IExpressionNode.
00540     // An expression can contain a 'TypeClauseNode IdentifierOrContextualToken', so it ought to be an IExpressionNode.
00541     //
00542     // If I open Visual Studio and I type "Person" into a C# file that is completely empty other than that text.
00543     // will it be treated as a type or a variable or something else?
00544     //
00545     // Because it seems that there is a pattern of either 'TypeClause' or 'TypeClauseNode IdentifierOrContextualToken'.
00546     //
00547     // And, the 'TypeClauseNode' could be made up of one or more ISyntaxToken.
00548     // 
00549     // It almost feels like you'd want to parse for 'TypeClause'
00550     // and 'TypeClauseNode IdentifierOrContextualToken'.
00551     // But in the sense of they both get the same starting point in the TokenWalker.
00552     // All the state is separate.
00553     //
00554     // Probably a 'bool TryParse_TypeClause_IdentifierOrContextualToken(out var aaa)'
00555     // and 'bool TryParse_TypeClause(out var aaa)'.
00556     //
00557     // You'd maybe invoke 'TryParse_TypeClause_IdentifierOrContextualToken' first,
00558     // then reset the TokenWalker state back to what it was and invoke
00559     // TryParse_TypeClause' to see that returns true/successful.
00560     //
00561     // Visual Studio treats the text "Person" when it is the only text in a C# file to be:
00562     // "The type or namespace name 'Person' could not be found (are you missing a using directive or an assembly reference?)
00563     //
00564     // If I open the demo website and put the same text into an empty C# file what is it treated as?
00565     // With the 'v 0.9.7.1 :: Release :: Luthetus.Ide.RazorLib' demo it is a Type for the syntax highlighting
00566     // and has a similar error diagnostic with "type or namespace could not be found" wording.
00567     //
